{"title":"MAHLE SmartBike Systems Launches New XS eBike System without Internal Battery","link":"https://bikerumor.com/mahle-smartbike-systems-xs-ebike-system-external-battery/","date":1730300400000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Mahle-XS-System-XS-System-render-jpeg.webp\" width=\"1280\" height=\"735\" alt=\"(Photos / MAHLE SmartBike Systems)\" /></p>\n<p>The German company <a href=\"https://mahle-smartbike.com/\" target=\"_blank\">MAHLE SmartBike Systems</a> specializes in ultralight, compact eBike systems. Today, they launched the new <a href=\"https://mahle-smartbike.com/XS/\" target=\"_blank\">XS System</a>. This new system consists of only essential eBike components – without an internal battery.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Mahle-XS-System-highlighted-jpeg.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"721\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Mahle-XS-System-highlighted-jpeg.webp\" alt=\"Mahle XS System highlighted\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Mahle-XS-System-highlighted-jpeg.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Mahle-XS-System-highlighted-297x167.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Mahle-XS-System-highlighted-120x68.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Mahle-XS-System-highlighted-768x433.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Mahle-XS-System-highlighted-1200x675.webp 1200w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photos / MAHLE SmartBike Systems)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The XS System is meant to offer a combo of lightness, versatility, sustainability, and an “unrivaled power-to-weight ratio”. MAHLE claims the system weighs in at 2.5kg (5.5 lbs) with the smaller X20 hub motor.  The system includes the eX1 External Battery, XS Smart Controller, a choice of hub motor (X20 or X30), and a Torque Sensor.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Mahle-XS-System-gravel-roads-jpeg.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"853\" height=\"1280\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Mahle-XS-System-gravel-roads-jpeg.webp\" alt=\"Mahle XS System gravel roads\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Mahle-XS-System-gravel-roads-jpeg.webp 853w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Mahle-XS-System-gravel-roads-200x300.webp 200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Mahle-XS-System-gravel-roads-80x120.webp 80w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Mahle-XS-System-gravel-roads-768x1152.webp 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Mahle-XS-System-foldie-bike-jpeg.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"853\" height=\"1280\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Mahle-XS-System-foldie-bike-jpeg.webp\" alt=\"Mahle XS System foldie bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Mahle-XS-System-foldie-bike-jpeg.webp 853w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Mahle-XS-System-foldie-bike-200x300.webp 200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Mahle-XS-System-foldie-bike-80x120.webp 80w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Mahle-XS-System-foldie-bike-768x1152.webp 768w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The minimalist design is something MAHLE hopes will make it easy for bike brands to adopt when designing their eBikes. Especially the brands that use compact, foldable, or unconventional bike designs. It also makes for a lighter bike if you’d rather ride it without electric assist. Just remove the battery, and pedal away. You’ll have some added resistance from the motor, but it should be closer to a normal bike weight than many other ebike systems. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>eX1 External Battery</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Mahle-XS-System-in-use-jpeg.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Mahle-XS-System-in-use-jpeg.webp\" alt=\"Mahle XS System in use\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Mahle-XS-System-in-use-jpeg.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Mahle-XS-System-in-use-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Mahle-XS-System-in-use-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Mahle-XS-System-in-use-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Mahle-XS-System-in-use-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Mahle-XS-System-in-use-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The XS System only uses one power source, the eX1 external battery. The battery weighs in at 1kg and is shaped like a water bottle. This eliminates the need for an internally integrated battery.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Mahle-XS-System-commuter-dude-jpeg.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Mahle-XS-System-commuter-dude-jpeg.webp\" alt=\"Mahle XS System commuter dude\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Mahle-XS-System-commuter-dude-jpeg.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Mahle-XS-System-commuter-dude-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Mahle-XS-System-commuter-dude-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Mahle-XS-System-commuter-dude-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Mahle-XS-System-commuter-dude-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Mahle-XS-System-commuter-dude-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Mahle-XS-System-more-gravel-jpeg.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Mahle-XS-System-more-gravel-jpeg.webp\" alt=\"Mahle XS System more gravel\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Mahle-XS-System-more-gravel-jpeg.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Mahle-XS-System-more-gravel-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Mahle-XS-System-more-gravel-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Mahle-XS-System-more-gravel-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Mahle-XS-System-more-gravel-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Mahle-XS-System-more-gravel-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Custom options for the brands are widespread, as the XS System allows the addition of optional accessories like Duo, eShifters, and Pulsar One. The new system also uses the new Energy Hub charging platform. You can charge the eX1 External Battery with a regular USB-C port. This turns the eX1 into an external power source for other devices. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>MAHLE ONE Ecosystem</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Mahle-XS-System-black-bike-jpeg.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Mahle-XS-System-black-bike-jpeg.webp\" alt=\"Mahle XS System black bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Mahle-XS-System-black-bike-jpeg.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Mahle-XS-System-black-bike-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Mahle-XS-System-black-bike-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Mahle-XS-System-black-bike-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Mahle-XS-System-black-bike-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Mahle-XS-System-black-bike-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The user of the new XS System can also connect to the MAHLE ONE digital ecosystem. This can be done using a laptop, phone, or Apple Watch. This ecosystem enables multiple functions and provides a seamless blending of user and eBike.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Check out the MAHLE Website for more info. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://mahle-smartbike.com/\" target=\"_blank\">MAHLE-SmartBike.com</a></em></p>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/mahle-smartbike-systems-xs-ebike-system-external-battery/\">MAHLE SmartBike Systems Launches New XS eBike System without Internal Battery</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Ron Frazelle","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"eeb47936021443556945e7c470cc0af3e0ae5d34238b1bfb6108210d6b6ff94f","category":"Cycling"}